tin%20said%20teaching%20became%20an%20%26quot%3Banchor%26quot%3B%20that%20helped%20him%20find%20structure%20after%20leaving%20Big%20Tech.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20ago%2C%20after%20almost%2015%20years%20in%20tech%2C%20I%20left%20my%20job%20as%20head%20of%20design%20studio%20at%20Airbnb%20in%20search%20of%20something%20new.%20It%20didn't%20go%20quite%20as%20I'd%20planned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-early-career-advice-mistakes-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etech%20career%3C%2Fa%3E%20began%20in%202006%20when%20I%20co-founded%20an%20ill-fated%20startup.%20After%20finishing%20a%20Ph.D.%20at%20UC%20Berkeley%20in%202010%2C%20I%20joined%20Yahoo%20and%20then%20moved%20to%20Meta%2C%20then%20known%20as%20Facebook%3Cspan%3E%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20as%20a%20UX%20researcher%20in%202012.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20joined%20Meta%20at%20a%20time%20of%20immense%20growth%20and%20worked%20on%20projects%20like%20the%20shift%20to%20mobile%2C%20the%20first%20feed%20ads%2C%20and%20integrating%20news%20into%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20three%20years%2C%20in%202015%2C%20I%20moved%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbnb-ceo-most-workers-dont-want-full-autonomy-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAirbnb%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20head%20of%20research.%20During%20my%20almost%20eight%20years%20there%2C%20I%20had%20a%20variety%20of%20executive%20roles%20in%20research%2C%20design%2C%20and%20product.%20I%20worked%20directly%20with%20the%20C-suite%20on%20top-level%20projects.%20I%20couldn't%20have%20asked%20for%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20burnout%20was%20in%20the%20rearview%20mirror%2C%20gaining%20on%20me.%20The%20guard%20was%20changing%20at%20Airbnb%20as%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20executives%20arrived.%20Many%20of%20us%20have%20had%20colleagues%20who've%20hung%20on%20at%20a%20company%20too%20long%20and%20become%20cynical%20despite%20their%20best%20intentions.%20I%20sensed%20it%20coming%20for%20me%2C%20and%20desperately%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20that%20guy.%20So%20I%20jumped%20ship%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20I'd%20feel%20relieved%20about%20leaving%2C%20and%20I%20do.%20But%20I've%20also%20struggled%20with%20a%20harsh%20realization%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbi-today-big-tech-companies-major-changes-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20tech%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20defined%20a%20core%20part%20of%20me.%20Leaving%20Big%20Tech%20forced%20me%20to%20re-evaluate%20what%20it%20means%20to%20be%20satisfied%2C%20productive%2C%20and%20useful.%20It's%20been%20harder%20than%20I%20imagined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c71e6669-0e3a-4c67-8435-416bd99caee7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeaving%20Big%20Tech%20meant%20I%20had%20to%20rewire%20my%20approach%20to%20satisfaction%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20left%20Airbnb%2C%20I%20hoped%20to%20consult%20and%20teach%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20concrete%20plan.%20For%20the%20first%20few%20months%2C%20I%20lived%20off%20savings%20and%20my%20wife's%20income%20before%20diving%20into%20new%20areas%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20I%20left%2C%20I%20began%20to%20realize%20how%20much%20the%20industry's%20expectations%20impacted%20my%20sense%20of%20satisfaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20expectations%20started%20with%20my%20time%20%E2%80%94%20how%20I%20should%20work%20and%20how%20much%20I%20should%20work.%20I've%20never%20worked%20for%20Elon%20Musk%20as%20part%20of%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-musks-midnight-email-telling-twitter-staff-work-long-hours-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bhardcore%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20work%20culture%2C%20but%20Meta%20and%20Airbnb%20were%20both%20intense%20and%20fast-paced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirbnb%20was%20particularly%20chaotic.%20I%20worked%20long%20hours%20and%20my%20calendar%20was%20stacked%20with%20meetings%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20was%20last-minute%20changes%2C%20ever-shifting%20priorities%2C%20and%20constant%20firefighting%20that%20really%20took%20a%20toll.%20Tech%20trained%20me%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20work%20is%20never%20done%20and%20my%20shift%20is%20never%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech's%20definitions%20of%20success%20also%20got%20their%20claws%20into%20me.%20We%20drive%20metrics%2C%20crush%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrategies-to-make-setting-company-okrs-easier-according-to-ceo-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOKRs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20launch%20on%20time%20at%20all%20costs.%20If%20we%20can't%20measure%20it%2C%20then%20it%20didn't%20happen.%20As%20employees%2C%20we're%20asked%20to%20judge%20ourselves%20and%20our%20worth%20by%20these%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20when%20I%20left%20my%20job%2C%20it%20all%20changed%20overnight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20struggled%20to%20reconstruct%20my%20sense%20of%20satisfaction%20without%20the%20usual%20signals.%20My%20hours%20were%20my%20own.%20There%20were%20no%20meetings%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20take%20and%20no%20goals%20except%20the%20ones%20I%20set%20for%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%20that%20my%20empty%20calendar%20left%20me%20with%20more%20anxiety%20than%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20I'd%20be%20able%20to%20detach%20from%20the%20%26quot%3Balways-on%26quot%3B%20work%20culture%2C%20but%20years%20of%20training%20made%20it%20hard%20to%20put%20down%20my%20phone.%20I%20made%20personal%20lists%20and%20goals%20to%20replicate%20the%20feeling%20of%20success%20that%20business%20metrics%20had%20given%20me%2C%20but%20I%20often%20found%20myself%20feeling%20unproductive%20and%20unsatisfied%20nonetheless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20retrospect%2C%20it's%20obvious%20the%20industry's%20expectations%20were%20unhealthy%20for%20me.%20It%20wasn't%20just%20the%20stress%20and%20anxiety%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-paying-jobs-for-people-who-thrive-under-pressure-2016-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-pressure%20career%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20was%20the%20narrow%20way%20that%20Big%20Tech%20defined%20what%20it%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20useful%2C%20productive%2C%20successful%20individual.%20Faced%20with%20the%20opportunity%20to%20redefine%20what%20those%20things%20meant%20to%20me%2C%20I%20found%20it%20hard%20to%20push%20the%20Big%20Tech%20definitions%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229a646b34-f28b-4fa0-86a7-f354f896c0d0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdjusting%20to%20life%20after%20Big%20Tech%20takes%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20found%20a%20silver%20bullet%20for%20the%20challenges%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-big-tech-job-uber-entrepreneur-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransitioning%20out%20of%20Big%20Tech%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20two%20years%20on%2C%20I've%20made%20significant%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20biggest%20discoveries%20was%20the%20importance%20of%20structure%20in%20the%20transition.%20I%20create%20that%20structure%20with%20what%20I%20call%20an%20%26quot%3Banchor%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20an%20activity%20that%20creates%20a%20rhythm%2C%20even%20though%20it%20might%20not%20take%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20probably%20not%20hitting%20the%20gym%2C%20reading%20a%20lot%2C%20or%20spending%20time%20with%20the%20kids.%20Those%20things%20are%20wonderful.%20But%20I%20think%20the%20best%20anchors%20are%20%3Cem%3Ework-like.%20%3C%2Fem%3ESomeone's%20expecting%20you%20to%20show%20up%20and%20do%20something%2C%20and%20you're%20excited%20about%20doing%20it.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20find%20one%20in%20learning%20a%20new%20skill%2C%20volunteering%20your%20time%2C%20or%20joining%20a%20group%20in%20your%20community.%20As%20long%20as%20it's%20a%20structured%20obligation%20that%20brings%20you%20joy%2C%20it'll%20do%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20my%20anchor%20in%20a%20love%20of%20teaching.%20I'm%20a%20lecturer%20in%20leadership%2C%20social%20psychology%2C%20and%20UX%20at%20the%20School%20of%20Information%20at%20UC%20Berkeley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20teach%20just%20one%20class%20a%20semester%2C%20but%20I%20love%20doing%20it.%20The%20cadence%20of%20preparing%2C%20teaching%2C%20and%20meeting%20with%20students%20grounds%20me.%20The%20deep%20sense%20of%20satisfaction%20it%20gives%20me%20is%20nothing%20like%20what%20my%20former%20career%20provided%2C%20and%20that's%20essential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20of%20my%20time%20is%20spent%20on%20executive%20coaching%2C%20consulting%2C%20and%20advising%20%E2%80%94%20all%20wonderful%20things%20that%20I'm%20thrilled%20to%20do%2C%20but%20all%20fundamentally%20unstructured%20and%20open-ended.%20Without%20the%20regular%20cadence%20of%20teaching%2C%20I%20think%20I'd%20feel%20unmoored.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdjusting%20to%20life%20after%20Big%20Tech%20tech%20takes%20time.%20The%20relief%20and%20a%20sense%20of%20freedom%20to%20build%20a%20new%20career%20might%20be%20mixed%20with%20anxiety%20around%20your%20hours%20being%20your%20own%2C%20your%20goals%20being%20in%20progress%2C%20and%20your%20calendar%20being%20empty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20normal%2C%20maybe%20even%20healthy.%20You're%20going%20through%20withdrawal.%20If%20you've%20left%20Big%20Tech%20and%20feel%20that%20same%20anxiety%20I%20did%2C%20maybe%20now%20you%20can%20put%20your%20finger%20on%20the%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20not%20doing%20a%20thing%20wrong.%20A%20change%20is%20underway.%20Reprogramming%20deeply%20engrained%20patterns%20is%20a%20tough%20job.%20But%20I%20suspect%20that%2C%20like%20me%2C%20you'll%20find%20it's%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Insider%20approached%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3EAirbnb%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3Efor%20comment.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaving-big-tech-