sh%20Columbia%2C%20Canada%2C%20and%20when%20they%20started%20thinking%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadoption-is-my-first-choice-for-motherhood-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadopting%20a%20child%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20me%20%E2%80%94%20they%20decided%20they%20needed%20to%20be%20in%20a%20more%20rural%20setting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20little%20town%20of%20Tsawwassen%20fit%20that%20bill.%20It%20had%20a%20good%20school%20system%20and%20was%20vibrant%20and%20up-and-coming.%20So%2C%20in%20late%201968%2C%20they%20purchased%20the%20land%20and%20built%20the%20house.%20It%20was%20finished%20in%20the%20summer%20of%201969.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20is%20a%20very%20German-looking%20style.%20Dad%20was%20Scottish%2C%20but%20I%20think%20he%20just%20liked%20the%20look%20of%20it.%20There's%20brick%20on%20the%20bottom%20frontage%20and%20stucco%20with%20what%20used%20to%20be%20dark%20brown%20trim.%20It's%20a%20double-story%20building%20with%20five%20bedrooms%20and%20a%20den.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220c5bf430-7209-4586-b8d4-3065fc66d88d%5C%22%3EI%20loved%20growing%20up%20in%20this%20house%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20adopting%20me%2C%20my%20parents%20brought%20me%20home%20from%20the%20hospital%20at%20the%20end%20of%20September%201969.%20The%20house%20would%20have%20been%20big%20for%20us%20%E2%80%94%20back%20then%2C%20it%20was%20just%20two%20adults%20and%20a%20tiny%20baby.%20My%20older%20brother%20John%20was%2020%20and%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouldnt-wait-to-leave-hometown-growing-up-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealready%20left%20home%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20more%20or%20less%20an%20only%20child%2C%20so%20I%20had%20free%20rein%20of%20the%20house.%20It's%20shaped%20like%20a%20U%20with%20this%20big%20porch%20in%20the%20center%2C%20and%20playing%20out%20there%20was%20every%20kid's%20dream.%20I%20remember%20whipping%20around%20on%20all%20sorts%20of%20different%20toys%20and%20bikes.%20There%20was%20a%20fairly%20big%20backyard%2C%20too%2C%20so%20there%20was%20always%20room%20to%20run%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20time%20my%20wife%20Cori%20and%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-to-talk-about-before-getting-engaged-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egot%20engaged%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20both%20of%20my%20parents'%20health%20tanked.%20We%20decided%20we%20would%20live%20with%20them%20so%20that%20they%20could%20remain%20in%20the%20home%20they'd%20built%20for%20as%20long%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20experienced%20many%20milestones%20in%20that%20house%2C%20both%20good%20and%20bad.%20When%20I%20married%20Cori%2C%20the%20house%20was%20the%20drop-off%20point%20for%20my%20groomsmen.%20We%20welcomed%20our%20four%20children%20while%20living%20there%20and%20navigated%20the%20passing%20of%20my%20dad%20in%202004%20and%20my%20mom%20in%202015.%20Since%20then%2C%20we've%20had%20engagement%20parties%20for%20two%20of%20our%20kids%20at%20the%20house%20and%20hosted%20a%20baby%20shower%20for%20our%20granddaughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20all%20of%20the%20house's%20quirks%2C%20and%20there's%20a%20deep%20familiarity%20there.%20We%20have%20friends%20who%20are%20still%20amazed%20when%20they%20find%20out%20we're%20still%20in%20the%20same%20place.%20Life%20doesn't%20usually%20allow%20that%20anymore%2C%20whether%20it's%20jobs%2C%20kids%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibecession-is-over-fake-politics-consumer-confidence-economy-feelings-sentiment-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20upheaval%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20feel%20very%20fortunate%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20consider%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20neighbors%20to%20be%20like%20family.%20Many%20of%20them%20have%20lived%20around%20us%20for%20easily%2030%20years%20or%20more.%20It's%20only%20recently%20that%20a%20few%20new%20ones%20are%20coming%20in%2C%20while%20the%20old%20ones%20are%